A major announcement is expected when embattled Cape Town Mayor Patricia de Lille and Democratic Alliance (DA) leader Mmusi Maimane hold a joint media conference in Cape Town shortly.   This follows a long legal and political tussle between De Lille and the DA. The DA-controlled city council has stripped her of her executive powers but failed to remove her in a motion of no confidence. The council deferred a second motion pending a DA disciplinary hearing against her. The party tried to terminate her membership but she challenged this successfully in court. It’s believed that Maimane and De Lille could announce an agreement. SABC News reporter Lukhanyo Calata with the latest…  Related Video: 